__NUXT_JSONP__("/gallery/bling-thing", (function(a,b){return {data:[{document:{date:b,title:[{type:"heading3",text:"Bling Thing",spans:[]}],photo:{dimensions:{width:800,height:898},alt:b,copyright:b,url:"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.prismic.io\u002Ffunk\u002F3ce6d2c6-feaa-4a74-8280-240640060b57_Bling+Thing.jpg?auto=compress,format",small:{dimensions:{width:320,height:359},alt:b,copyright:b,url:"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.prismic.io\u002Ffunk\u002F3ce6d2c6-feaa-4a74-8280-240640060b57_Bling+Thing.jpg?auto=compress,format&rect=0,0,800,898&w=320&h=359"}},content:[{type:a,text:"18 Carat white gold, 30 grams\nMirror polish\nGreen Tsavorite eyes (of garnet family)\nEngraving inside band: “Leap of Faith”\nPrice: sell the Merc :-)",spans:[]},{type:a,text:"But this isn’t even the expensive one…\nThe owner of the studio where I work has an amazing daughter, Pam, who designs, markets and sells high end jewelry.\nShe  walks in one day with a MASSIVE bird ring on her finger… same size as  this one above, but with the addition of a couple hundred tiny diamonds  and sapphires. Absolutely stunning.\nSo I asks her what’s her friendly  price (like Valentine’s day’s comin’ up soon…) and she says “Fifty” and  I’m feeling great cause I happened to have a 50 Euro note on me which I  whipped out and slapped on the table…\nOK, the look she gave me said “ummm, it’s the fifty with the big K after it… duh-uh !”\nOoops.",spans:[]},{type:a,text:"Meanwhile,  an artist at the studio doing her first big album fell in love with the  ring and also made the mistake of asking how much…\nBut there was a solution. Make a duplicate ring, but without the stones.\nWhich  came to pass and the finished ring was presented today, in the bar of  Studio C, with pink Champagne and there were smiles all around and  everyone lived happily eva afta :-))",spans:[]},{type:a,text:"But before handing it over,  there needed to be pictures. I set up my studio flash and stuff and  reeled off 20-some macro shots, one or two of which did it justice (I  hope)… and another 10 or so with the ring on the creator’s finger.",spans:[]},{type:a,text:"But that’s NOT what this picture is.",spans:[]},{type:a,text:"I  found a shot I took of my daughter Melanie in her teens, looked kinda  classy... so I took one of the shots of the duplicate ring on Pam's  finger and placed it in the foreground while adding blur to the shot of  Melanie to give the semblance of depth.",spans:[]},{type:a,text:"So you CAN wear the ring and keep the Merc :-)",spans:[]},{type:a,text:"Background portrait of Melanie: Canon EOS 100 + EF 100 mm fixed focal on Fuji Reala 100 ISO color print film.",spans:[]},{type:a,text:"Pam's ringed hand: Canon EOS 5D MkI + EF 100 mm fixed focal.",spans:[]}],tag:"portrait montage"}}],fetch:[],mutations:void 0}}("paragraph",null)));